&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Noah Levitt&lt;nlevitt@...&gt;  wrote:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Hello Markus,
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Thanks for this report, you&#39;ve brought to light a bug in the code and a
&gt;&gt; mistake in the documentation which conspired to produce this obtuse error.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; First problem is the exception you got:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; java.lang.IllegalStateException: Can&#39;t overwrite cause
&gt;&gt; 	at java.lang.Throwable.initCause(Throwable.java:320)
&gt;&gt; 	at org.archive.spring.Sheet.prime(Sheet.java:152)
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; It was thrown in the process of handling the real exception, preventing
&gt;&gt; the real stack trace from making it into the log. I&#39;ve checked in a fix
&gt;&gt; for that - https://webarchive.jira.com/source/changelog/HER?cs=7235
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; With that change in place, the real problem is revealed:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; 2011-08-30T22:56:24.688Z SEVERE Failed to convert property value of type
&gt;&gt; &#39;java.lang.String&#39; to required type
&gt;&gt; &#39;org.archive.modules.canonicalize.UriCanonicalizationPolicy&#39; for
&gt;&gt; property &#39;canonicalizationPolicy&#39;;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; As you mentioned, you were using this snippet as recommended by the wiki
&gt;&gt; page:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; &lt;entry key=&#39;preparer.canonicalizationPolicy&#39;
&gt;&gt; value=&#39;altCanonicalizationPolicy&#39;/&gt;  &lt;!-- wrong --&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; But instead it should look like this:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; &lt;entry key=&#39;preparer.canonicalizationPolicy&#39;&gt;
&gt;&gt; &lt;ref bean=&#39;altCanonicalizationPolicy&#39;/&gt;
&gt;&gt; &lt;/entry&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; I&#39;ve fixed the doc.
&gt;&gt; https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/URI+Canonicalization+Rules
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Noah
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; On 08/30/2011 12:28 PM, mirschi74 wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt; Hi,
&gt;&gt;&gt;
